core_requirement:
The following disposal and recycling information shall be marked on or supplied with the battery system:

a) Storage and disposal instructions shall be provided;

b) Special disposal instructions about the battery system shall be included, emphasizing proper recycling and disposal procedures;

c) Instructions shall state that users should heed enclosed special disposal instructions about the battery system;

d) Recommended storage conditions shall be specified:
   1) Recommended storage temperature: −10 °C to below 30 °C (if not otherwise specified by the supplier);
   2) Store at dry places, away from open flames and food;
   3) Avoid large temperature changes;
   4) Do not store close to heating devices, avoid direct sunlight;
   5) Preferred storage at 50% of the nominal capacity (if not otherwise specified by the supplier);
   6) Temperature above 70 °C may result in battery leakage and rupture (if not otherwise specified by the supplier);

e) Instructions shall state: do not open, chop up or disassemble rechargeable battery systems at any times;

f) Keep original printed papers with product information for later consultation;

g) IF the battery system is removed from the device: if possible, remove battery systems from device if they are not being needed;

h) Recommended charging instructions shall be provided.

